reviewText: Beautiful story about the folks of Ireland.  It talks about the everyday lives of those who live there as well as the history of Ireland as told by those who saw it first hand. The stories are both touching and humorous, with each person having their own special story to share.
Its not in a format that I could open and watch.

I saw this in a theater in Syracuse, New York.
It was charming and touched my little Irish heart.
Did not know it was region 2. Cannot view. And have never received Buchanan DVDs.
